{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"iptyzetmct98konuehjlmc3","title":"Types","desc":"","updated":1671814716487,"created":1671811133127,"custom":{},"fname":"programing.rust.advanced.types","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"},"contentHash":"cbe40303bea1f4873b2abfc3842131fc","links":[],"anchors":{"advanced-types":{"type":"header","text":"Advanced Types","value":"advanced-types","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1},"using-the-newtype-pattern-for-type-safety-and-abstraction":{"type":"header","text":"Using the Newtype Pattern for Type Safety and Abstraction","value":"using-the-newtype-pattern-for-type-safety-and-abstraction","line":11,"column":0,"depth":2},"creating-type-synonyms-with-type-aliases":{"type":"header","text":"Creating Type Synonyms with Type Aliases","value":"creating-type-synonyms-with-type-aliases","line":16,"column":0,"depth":2},"the-never-type-that-never-return":{"type":"header","text":"The Never Type that Never Return","value":"the-never-type-that-never-return","line":55,"column":0,"depth":2},"dynamically-sized-types-and-the-sized-trait":{"type":"header","text":"Dynamically Sized Types and the Sized Trait","value":"dynamically-sized-types-and-the-sized-trait","line":67,"column":0,"depth":2},"the-str-type":{"type":"header","text":"The str type","value":"the-str-type","line":84,"column":0,"depth":3}},"children":[],"parent":"ey8rquqb5xn9ovglgr54z80","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"types\">Types<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#types\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"advanced-types\">Advanced Types<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#advanced-types\"></a></h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch19-04-advanced-types.html\">https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch19-04-advanced-types.html</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2 id=\"using-the-newtype-pattern-for-type-safety-and-abstraction\">Using the Newtype Pattern for Type Safety and Abstraction<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#using-the-newtype-pattern-for-type-safety-and-abstraction\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>We can use the newtype pattern to abstract away some implementation details of a type: the new type can <strong>expose a public API</strong> that is different from the API of the private inner type.</li>\n<li>Newtypes can also hide internal implementation</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"creating-type-synonyms-with-type-aliases\">Creating Type Synonyms with Type Aliases<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#creating-type-synonyms-with-type-aliases\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Type alias: to give an <strong>exising type another name</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<pre class=\"language-rust\"><code class=\"language-rust\"><span class=\"token keyword\">fn</span> <span class=\"token function-definition function\">main</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">type</span> <span class=\"token type-definition class-name\">Kilometers</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">i32</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// the type Kilometers will be treated the same as values of type i32</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> x<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">i32</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> y<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Kilometers</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token macro property\">println!</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"x + y = {}\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> x <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> y<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// the compiler will not give us an error when we mix up 2 types</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre>\n<pre class=\"language-rust\"><code class=\"language-rust\"><span class=\"token keyword\">fn</span> <span class=\"token function-definition function\">main</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// Thunk can be used as an alias for the type Box&#x3C;dyn Fn() + Send + 'static></span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">type</span> <span class=\"token type-definition class-name\">Thunk</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Box</span><span class=\"token operator\">&#x3C;</span><span class=\"token keyword\">dyn</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Fn</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Send</span> <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token lifetime-annotation symbol\">'static</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> f<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Thunk</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Box</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">::</span><span class=\"token function\">new</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token closure-params\"><span class=\"token closure-punctuation punctuation\">|</span><span class=\"token closure-punctuation punctuation\">|</span></span> <span class=\"token macro property\">println!</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"hi\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">fn</span> <span class=\"token function-definition function\">takes_long_type</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>f<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Thunk</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"token comment\">// --snip--</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">fn</span> <span class=\"token function-definition function\">returns_long_type</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">-></span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Thunk</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"token comment\">// --snip--</span>\n        <span class=\"token class-name\">Box</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">::</span><span class=\"token function\">new</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token closure-params\"><span class=\"token closure-punctuation punctuation\">|</span><span class=\"token closure-punctuation punctuation\">|</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre>\n<ul>\n<li>Common alias for the <code>Result</code>:\n<pre class=\"language-rust\"><code class=\"language-rust\"><span class=\"token comment\">// We can use any methods that work on Result&#x3C;T, E>, as well as special syntax like the ? operator</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">type</span> <span class=\"token type-definition class-name\">Result</span><span class=\"token operator\">&#x3C;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">T</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token namespace\">std<span class=\"token punctuation\">::</span>result<span class=\"token punctuation\">::</span></span><span class=\"token class-name\">Result</span><span class=\"token operator\">&#x3C;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">T</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token namespace\">std<span class=\"token punctuation\">::</span>io<span class=\"token punctuation\">::</span></span><span class=\"token class-name\">Error</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"the-never-type-that-never-return\">The Never Type that Never Return<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#the-never-type-that-never-return\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><code>!</code> ~ <em>empty type</em> because it has no values, or the <em>never type</em> because it stands in the place of the return type when a function will <strong>never return</strong>.</li>\n<li>Functions that return never are called <em>diverging functions</em>.  \n<pre class=\"language-rust\"><code class=\"language-rust\"><span class=\"token comment\">// we can't create values of the type ! -> bar can never possibly return</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">fn</span> <span class=\"token function-definition function\">bar</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">-></span> <span class=\"token operator\">!</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// --snip--</span>\n    <span class=\"token macro property\">panic!</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"dynamically-sized-types-and-the-sized-trait\">Dynamically Sized Types and the Sized Trait<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#dynamically-sized-types-and-the-sized-trait\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Rust needs to know certain details about its types, such as <strong>how much space to allocate</strong> for a value of a particular type.</li>\n<li>Dynamically sized types (unsized types): let us write code using values whose size we can know only at <strong>runtime</strong>.</li>\n<li>Dynamically sized types in Rust have an extra bit of <strong>metadata that stores the size</strong> of the dynamic information. (we must always put values of dynamically sized types <strong>behind a pointer</strong> of some kind)</li>\n<li>The <code>Sized</code> trait to determine whether or not a type's size is <strong>known at compile time</strong>. \n<ul>\n<li>\n<pre class=\"language-rust\"><code class=\"language-rust\"><span class=\"token keyword\">fn</span> <span class=\"token function-definition function\">generic</span><span class=\"token operator\">&#x3C;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">T</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>t<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">T</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n~\n<span class=\"token keyword\">fn</span> <span class=\"token function-definition function\">generic</span><span class=\"token operator\">&#x3C;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">T</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Sized</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>t<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">T</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n<li>relax the restriction\n<pre class=\"language-rust\"><code class=\"language-rust\"><span class=\"token keyword\">fn</span> <span class=\"token function-definition function\">generic</span><span class=\"token operator\">&#x3C;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">T</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token operator\">?</span><span class=\"token class-name\">Sized</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>t <span class=\"token operator\">&#x26;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">T</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// T may or may not be Sized</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n<li>The <code>?Trait</code> syntax with this meaning is only available for <code>Sized</code></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"the-str-type\">The <code>str</code> type<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#the-str-type\"></a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><code>str</code> is a <em>dynamically sized type</em>. We can't know how long the string until runtime</li>\n</ul>\n<pre class=\"language-rust\"><code class=\"language-rust\"><span class=\"token keyword\">fn</span> <span class=\"token function-definition function\">main</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// this will cause a compiler error</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// Rust need to know the data size of the str type, but s1 and s2 have different length</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> s1<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">str</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Hello there!\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> s2<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">str</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"How's it going?\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre>\n<ul>\n<li><code>&#x26;T</code>: is a single value that <strong>stores the memory address</strong> of where the <code>T</code> is located.</li>\n<li><code>&#x26;str</code> has 2 value\n<ul>\n<li>the address if the str</li>\n<li>its length</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"xfkxbponh0sohobo6pual15","title":"Root","desc":"","updated":1668137379975,"created":1663481872547,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"},"contentHash":"cb44915142ec96bef8f764f3dc90389e","links":[],"anchors":{"welcome-to-my-page":{"type":"header","text":"Welcome to my page","value":"welcome-to-my-page","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1},"contacts":{"type":"header","text":"Contacts","value":"contacts","line":12,"column":0,"depth":2},"dendron":{"type":"header","text":"Dendron","value":"dendron","line":18,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["u5a2e2vvfn3x7k0shuvmb1b","qw8y69zxn8wr7tzz4gtcrrv","q7qw45jglqwmynary64q67c","6wjqcjgkrpeqtmzb1o8o1q8","3ervbn5we7t8v2l2vwtx847","4qi2z0z9fquupbd651xausx","sencgim78q74o1zuyvy1vz7","ue4oml1si982t3mmbthyxi9","zrogwjgtze8ne5joqpz8ty9","oesia0lbzh03fsoy124ck0k","el3p9zjue6h3b6zsl9oejkt","t5grkmcwvu4nl43igsj4gxz"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"# Welcome to my page\n\n- This is a place where I write my knowledge in both Vietnamese and English.\n- Please feel free to correct me if there is anything not right.\n\n## Contacts\n\n- [Github](https://github.com/thanhpp)\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/ugNRjFNqjp)\n- [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/in/thanhpp/)\n\n## Dendron\n\n- [Home Page](https://wiki.dendron.so/)"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":5,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2":true,"enableSelfContainedVaults":true},"commands":{"lookup":{"note":{"selectionMode":"extract","confirmVaultOnCreate":true,"vaultSelectionModeOnCreate":"alwaysPrompt","leaveTrace":false,"bubbleUpCreateNew":true,"fuzzThreshold":0.2}},"r